   180	## Rotational Invariance
   181	Let the circle have radius $R$. The position of the chord is determined
   182	by giving the polar coordinates $(r, \theta)$ of its center. We seek to
   183	answer a more detailed question than Bertrand's: What probability
   184	density $f(r, \theta)dA = f(r, \theta) r dr d\theta$ should we assign
   185	over the interior area of the circle? The dependence on $\theta$ is
   186	actually irrelevant to Bertrand's question, since the distribution of
   187	chord lengths depends only on the radial distribution
   188	$$g(r) = \int_0^{2\pi} f(r, \theta)d\theta.$$
