Updated `content/papers/well.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

### What I changed
- Added explicit equation tags so all in-text equation references are discoverable on display equations:
  - `(1)` through `(13)` added via `\tag{...}`.
- Inserted blank-line paragraph breaks at clear prose transitions where adjacent paragraphs were previously joined.
- Improved markdown structure in back matter:
  - Converted Appendix entries into a clean markdown list.
  - Converted References entries into a clean markdown list.

### Self-check
- Paragraph boundaries now use blank lines where intended.
- All referenced equation numbers `(1)`–`(13)` are present on display equations.
- No abstract duplication was found in the body, so none removed.
- No figure work was done (as requested).
